  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I went to--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, married, and, and, as I mentioned earlier, lived on the campus of UCLA, and in a curriculum for mechanical engineering at UCLA.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there was a lot of math and, and engineering subjects and physics and chemistry, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I graduated in 1950, June of '50, and went to work immediately for a-- an appliance company in South Los Angeles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And had, had actually moved back to my mother's residence after we graduated-- mother's former residence.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we lived there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I drove into Los Angeles at this appliance company, but I had-- I had made the application to a-- to a place called AeroJet General in Azusa, California, east of Los Angeles.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I got tired of the commute to downtown Los Angeles, or South Los Angeles, and I accepted a position at Lockheed in Burbank.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I stayed there only for a couple of months, because I got an offer from Aerojet General, which was really where I wanted to go in the first place.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I, I started my career in rocket propulsion at Aerojet General in Azusa, California.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was assigned initially as a test engineer to test rockets-- rocket engines.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We tested several pretty advanced kinds of rockets that we were trying to develop using a, a mono-propellant, for instance.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Navy-- we were involved-- Aerojet was involved in assist takeoff units, solid rocket units.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were getting, in those days, in 1950 when I went to work-- '51, when I went to work for Aerojet-- they were trying to develop a-- an assist takeoff unit for the Navy, which was liquid rather than solid propellant.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they didn't like to have to buy propellants, like an oxidizer and a fuel on board a ship, particularly on a carrier.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
